<paragraph blockId="9.[136,1452,1450,1685]" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,465,1450,1477]" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">Distribution and habitat:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boissier" authorityYear="1860" box="[465,756,1451,1477]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peperomioides">
<emphasis box="[465,756,1451,1477]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">Euphorbia peperomioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[921,989,1451,1477]" name="Brazil" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1004,1160,1451,1477]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1171,1287,1451,1477]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1299,1378,1451,1477]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">Paraná</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion country="Brazil" name="Santa Catarina" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">Santa Catarina</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[285,498,1485,1512]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
). In the state of 
<collectingRegion box="[677,790,1485,1512]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="9" pageNumber="202">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
the species occurs on high montane habitats, frequently on swampy areas or riversides.
</paragraph>
